transcript.text: Hello, welcome to on Print shop.
This video is about departments and customers.
In this video we will see how to add departments and customers, how to import customer for specific store and how to create approver rights to a specific customer.
First of all let's understand what the department means.
Let's say when you are setting up a private store, there may be many departments like HR, Admin, technical and you can assign specific employee in a particular department.
Let's see how easily you can add department under a private store and how you can assign specific customer under the department.
Just go to store management then click on store, select the store, click on action and edit.
Here you can see the button named as the department.
Just activate it and click on save button.
As you will click on the save button, you will be able to see the tab of department.
Then by clicking on add button you can add number of departments.
There are no such restrictions right now you can see there are two departments added to add department, click on add button, put department name then to e-mail.
And there is also cost center code you can enter if you want.
And last you just need to enter pay on limit like how much of amount you want to add to this department and click on the save button.
Now let's see how we can add customer to a specific store.

And under specific department just click on customer click on add button and you need to select user type to select store name and then select department to keep customer under specific department and just fill other details.
For bulk import of customer just click on the import button.
And you need to follow 3 easy steps.
Step one download the sheet let me open the excel sheet here you need to put all data here.
Be careful when you are filling country.
So here instead of putting country name you need to put country code which you will get in Step 2.
Suppose you are from United States.
So here you can see the country code of United States is 223.
So instead of putting USA you need to put 223.
For store ID and department ID you can find out here.
Just fill out the excel sheet and import it.
That's it.
Lastly, in private stores there are some managerial approval requirements.
Let's say if an employee is placing the order first, it should go to the manager.
If the manager approves it, then only it should go to the printer.
If the manager rejects the order, it won't go to the printer.
So we can set this kind of approval process in our system with a multi level hierarchy.

To set this just go to customers, click on access roles, select the person to whom you want to give managerial role, click on Allow access for specific department or all department and click on order approval permission.
So here you can see the multi level hierarchy if you have created a person as a super approver.
So whenever any employee will place an order, it will first go to the manager.
If the manager approves it then only it will fall in printer's grid.
Also to approve, the manager doesn't need to log in into the system every time he will receive an e-mail.
He can directly approve it from e-mail without logging into the system.
Thank you.
If you have any concerns, please connect with us at support at on printshop.com.
